Phase 1 broker IP validation
Date: 2026-04-14
Status: CONFIRMED

Config under test:
- configs/data.yaml windowing.broker_context.broker_ip = 192.168.1.7
- configs/data.yaml windowing.broker_context.broker_port = 1883

Method:
1. Inspect MQTT-IoT-IDS2020 packet_features CSVs.
2. Filter rows where src_port == 1883 or dst_port == 1883.
3. Count the broker-side IP candidate from src_ip when src_port == 1883 and from dst_ip when dst_port == 1883.

Observed broker-side IP counts:
- normal: total 1883 rows = 906412; top candidate = 192.168.1.7 (906412 / 100.00%)
- scan_A: total 1883 rows = 64022; top candidate = 192.168.1.7 (64022 / 100.00%)
- scan_sU: total 1883 rows = 191060; top candidate = 192.168.1.7 (191060 / 100.00%)
- sparta: total 1883 rows = 693157; top candidate = 192.168.1.7 (693157 / 100.00%)
- mqtt_bruteforce: total 1883 rows = 8183214; top candidate = 192.168.1.7 (8183214 / 100.00%)

Interpretation:
- The stable broker-facing MQTT endpoint is 192.168.1.7 across every scenario when restricted to broker port 1883.
- mqtt_bruteforce.csv contains other traffic early in the file (for example DNS rows involving 192.168.2.1), but those rows are outside the 1883-based broker test and do not contradict the broker candidate.

Decision:
- Keep broker_ip = 192.168.1.7.
- No config update was needed.
